Three Crowns Milk has revealed plans to reward its Muslim consumers with Ramadan gift boxes. The company said in a statement that the gift boxes would include fruits and other nutritious items needed to keep them nourished and energised during the fast. In a newly-launched campaign, tagged ‘Three Crowns supports your heart’, the company said it would be engaging Muslim consumers through a series of rewarding activities during the holy month of Ramadan. The Marketing Manager, Three Crowns, Gloria Jacobs, noted that Ramadan provided an opportunity for the brand to further connect with Muslims across the country. She said, “With this campaign, which runs from April 2nd – 30th, we aim to encourage the culture of giving associated with this period and promote the importance of healthy eating and lifestyle throughout the period of Ramadan and beyond. Jacobs stated that Muslim influencers would be engaged to highlight the importance of healthy eating and lifestyle during Ramadan with Three Crowns consumers. “These activities will be held on the social media pages of the brand and the influencers. Consumers can win exciting prizes when they join these influencers on their Instagram/Facebook live sessions, and answer questions correctly.”